mibatmIntfConfProfileTable.name: mibatmIntfConfProfileTable
mibatmIntfConfProfileTable.description: A list of mibatmIntfConfProfile profile entries.

mibatmIntfConfProfileEntry.name: mibatmIntfConfProfileEntry
mibatmIntfConfProfileEntry.description: A mibatmIntfConfProfile entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibatmIntfConfProfile profile.

atmIntfConfProfile_Address_PhysicalAddre.name: atmIntfConfProfile_Address_PhysicalAddress_Shelf
atmIntfConfProfile_Address_PhysicalAddre.description: The number of the shelf that the addressed physical device resides on.

atmIntfConfProfile_Address_PhysicalAddre.name: atmIntfConfProfile_Address_PhysicalAddress_Slot
atmIntfConfProfile_Address_PhysicalAddre.description: The number of the slot that the addressed physical device resides on.

atmIntfConfProfile_Address_PhysicalAddre.name: atmIntfConfProfile_Address_PhysicalAddress_ItemNumber
atmIntfConfProfile_Address_PhysicalAddre.description: A number that specifies an addressable entity within the context of shelf and slot.

atmIntfConfProfile_Address_LogicalItem.name: atmIntfConfProfile_Address_LogicalItem
atmIntfConfProfile_Address_LogicalItem.description: A number that specifies an addressable logical entity within the context of a physical address.

atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_MaxVpcs.name: atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_MaxVpcs
atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_MaxVpcs.description: The maximum number of VPCs (PVPCs/SVPCs) supported at this ATM interface.

atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_MaxVccs.name: atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_MaxVccs
atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_MaxVccs.description: The maximum number of VCCs (PVCCs/SVCCs) supported at this ATM interface.

atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_MaxActiveV.name: atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_MaxActiveVpiBits
atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_MaxActiveV.description: The maximum number of active VPI bits configured for use at this ATM interface.

atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_MaxActiveV.name: atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_MaxActiveVciBits
atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_MaxActiveV.description: The maximum number of active VCI bits configured for use at this ATM interface.

atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_IlmiVpi.name: atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_IlmiVpi
atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_IlmiVpi.description: The VPI value of the ILMI VCC at this ATM interface. If ilmi-vpi and ilmi-vci are both zero ILMI is not supported at this interface.

atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_IlmiVci.name: atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_IlmiVci
atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_IlmiVci.description: The VCI value of the ILMI VCC at this ATM interface. If ilmi-vpi and ilmi-vci are both zero ILMI is not supported at this interface.

atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_NeighborIp.name: atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_NeighborIpAddress
atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_NeighborIp.description: The IP address of the neighbor system connected to the far end of this interface, to which a Network Management Station can send SNMP messages, as IP datagrams sent to UDP port 161, in order to access network management information concerning the operation of that system. Note that the value of this object may be obtained in different ways, e.g., by manual configuration, or through ILMI interaction with the neighbor system.

atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_NeighborNa.name: atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_NeighborName
atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_NeighborNa.description: The textual name of the interface on the neighbor system on the far end of this interface, and to which this interface connects. If the neighbor system is manageable through SNMP and supports the object ifName, the value of this object must be identical with that of ifName for the ifEntry of the lowest level physical interface for this port. If this interface does not have a textual name, the value of this object is a zero length string. Note that the value of this object may be obtained in different ways, e.g., by manual configuration, or through ILMI interaction with the neighbor system.

atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_SubscAtmAd.name: atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_SubscAtmAddress
atmIntfConfProfile_BaseConfig_SubscAtmAd.description: The identifier assigned by a service provider to the network side of public network UNI. If this interface has no assigned service provider address, then atmInterfaceSubscrAddress is an octet string of zero length.

atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_Confi.name: atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_ConfigType
atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_Confi.description: The type of connection setup procedures configured for the ATM interface. Setting this variable to a value of 'other' is not allowed. Default value: autoConfig.

atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_Confi.name: atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_ConfigSide
atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_Confi.description: The configured role of the managed entity as one side of the ATM interface. This value does not apply when the object atmIntfConfigType is set to `autoConfig',`atmfPnni1Dot0', or `atmfBici2Dot0'.

atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_IlmiA.name: atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_IlmiAdminStatus
atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_IlmiA.description: Following ILMI components will be enabled on this port only if ilmi-admin-status is set to YES - ilmiAddressRegistration, - ilmiConnectivity, - ilmiPvcPvpMgmt, - ilmiSigVccParamNegotiation

atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_IlmiC.name: atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_IlmiConnectivity
atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_IlmiC.description: ILMI Connectivity enabled on this port if set to YES

atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_ConnE.name: atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_ConnEstabInterval
atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_ConnE.description: The amount of time S (in seconds ) between successive transmissions of ILMI messages on this interface for the purpose of detecting establishment of ILMI connectivity.

atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_LossD.name: atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_LossDetectInterval
atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_LossD.description: The amount of time T ( in seconds ) between successive transmissions of ILMI messages on this interface for the purpose of detecting loss of ILMI connectivity. The distinguished value zero disables ILMI connectivity procedures on this interface.

atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_PollI.name: atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_PollInactFactor
atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_PollI.description: The number K of consecutive polls on this interface for which no ILMI response message is received before ILMI connectivity is declared lost.

atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_Devic.name: atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_DeviceType
atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_Devic.description: Specifies whether this end of the interface is advertised in ILMI as a device of the `public' or `private' type.

atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_MaxSw.name: atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_MaxSwitchedVpcVpi
atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_MaxSw.description: The maximum VPI that the signalling stack on the ATM interface is configured to support for allocation to switched virtual path connections.

atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_MaxSw.name: atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_MaxSwitchedVccVpi
atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_MaxSw.description: The maximum VPI that the signalling stack on the ATM interface is configured to support for allocation to switched virtual channel connections.

atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_MinSw.name: atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_MinSwitchedVccVci
atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_MinSw.description: The minimum VCI that the signalling stack on the ATM interface is configured to support for allocation to switched virtual channel connections.

atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_SigVc.name: atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_SigVccRxQosName
atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_SigVc.description: The signalling VCC QOS parameters for the receive direction.

atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_SigVc.name: atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_SigVccTxQosName
atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_SigVc.description: The signalling VCC QOS parameters for the transmit direction.

atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_PvcFa.name: atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_PvcFailureTrapEnabled
atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_PvcFa.description: Allows the generation of traps in response to PVCL or PVPL failures on this interface. Default = FALSE

atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_PvcFa.name: atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_PvcFailureIntvl
atmIntfConfProfile_ExtensionConfig_PvcFa.description: The minimum interval between the sending of atmIntfPvcFailuresTrap notifications for this interface, Default = 30 seconds.
